    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nSee the repro below.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- `nvim --clean x.lua` \n- insert `local a = 1`, jump to `a`, type `van`.\n\nFor me `a = 1` becomes selected.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nOnly `a` should be selected (useful for example to ~rename a variable~ changing string contents etc.).\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nv0.12.0-dev-2727+gad4bc2d90c\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nn/a\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nDebian Sid\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\nfrom repo",
